    • Field Detail

      • deadline

        public Date deadline

        Deadline of the task, pending and running runs are resolved as exception if not resolved by other means before the deadline. Note, deadline cannot be more than 5 days into the future

        See https://schemas.taskcluster.net/hooks/v1/task-status.json#/properties/status/properties/deadline

      • expires

        public Date expires

        Task expiration, time at which task definition and status is deleted. Notice that all artifacts for the task must have an expiration that is no later than this.

        See https://schemas.taskcluster.net/hooks/v1/task-status.json#/properties/status/properties/expires

      • provisionerId

        public String provisionerId

        Unique identifier for the provisioner that this task must be scheduled on

        Syntax: ^([a-zA-Z0-9-_]*)$ Min length: 1 Max length: 22

        See https://schemas.taskcluster.net/hooks/v1/task-status.json#/properties/status/properties/provisionerId

      • retriesLeft

        public int retriesLeft

        Number of retries left for the task in case of infrastructure issues

        Mininum: 0 Maximum: 999

        See https://schemas.taskcluster.net/hooks/v1/task-status.json#/properties/status/properties/retriesLeft

      • runs

        public Status.RunInformation[] runs

        List of runs, ordered so that index i has runId == i

        See https://schemas.taskcluster.net/hooks/v1/task-status.json#/properties/status/properties/runs

      • schedulerId

        public String schedulerId

        Identifier for the scheduler that defined this task.

        Syntax: ^([a-zA-Z0-9-_]*)$ Min length: 1 Max length: 22

        See https://schemas.taskcluster.net/hooks/v1/task-status.json#/properties/status/properties/schedulerId

      • state

        public String state

        State of this task. This is just an auxiliary property derived from state of latests run, or unscheduled if none.

        Possible values: * “unscheduled” * “pending” * “running” * “completed” * “failed” * “exception”

        See https://schemas.taskcluster.net/hooks/v1/task-status.json#/properties/status/properties/state

      • taskGroupId

        public String taskGroupId

        Identifier for a group of tasks scheduled together with this task, by scheduler identified by schedulerId. For tasks scheduled by the task-graph scheduler, this is the taskGraphId.

        Syntax: ^[A-Za-z0-9_-]{8}[Q-T][A-Za-z0-9_-][CGKOSWaeimquy26-][A-Za-z0-9_-]{10}[AQgw]$

        See https://schemas.taskcluster.net/hooks/v1/task-status.json#/properties/status/properties/taskGroupId

      • taskId

        public String taskId

        Unique task identifier, this is UUID encoded as URL-safe base64 and stripped of = padding.

        Syntax: ^[A-Za-z0-9_-]{8}[Q-T][A-Za-z0-9_-][CGKOSWaeimquy26-][A-Za-z0-9_-]{10}[AQgw]$

        See https://schemas.taskcluster.net/hooks/v1/task-status.json#/properties/status/properties/taskId

      • workerType

        public String workerType

        Identifier for worker type within the specified provisioner

        Syntax: ^([a-zA-Z0-9-_]*)$ Min length: 1 Max length: 22

        See https://schemas.taskcluster.net/hooks/v1/task-status.json#/properties/status/properties/workerType
